theorem closure_eq_closure_interior_closure_interior_of_P2
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 A →
      closure (A : Set X) =
        closure (interior (closure (interior A))) := by
  intro hP2
  apply subset_antisymm
  · -- `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure (interior A)))`
    exact
      (Topology.P2_implies_closure_subset_closure_interior_closure_interior
        (X := X) (A := A)) hP2
  · -- `closure (interior (closure (interior A))) ⊆ closure A`
    -- First, relate to `closure (interior A)`.
    have h₁ :
        closure (interior (closure (interior (A : Set X)))) ⊆
          closure (interior (A : Set X)) := by
      have hInt :
          interior (closure (interior (A : Set X))) ⊆
            closure (interior (A : Set X)) :=
        Topology.interior_closure_interior_subset_closure_interior
          (X := X) (A := A)
      exact closure_mono hInt
    -- Second, use the basic inclusion `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A`.
    have h₂ :
        closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
      Topology.closure_interior_subset_closure_self (X := X) (A := A)
    exact h₁.trans h₂
